{"textColorIndex":0,"note":"MAIN PROGRAM STRUCTURE:\nDefine NetworkConfig class\n - Properties: DHCP settings, VLANs, DNS servers, firewall rules\n - Methods: validation, configuration loading\n\nDefine Device Management\n - Base NetworkDevice class (abstract)\n - Specific device classes (Router, Switch, AP) inherit from base\n - Each device implements deploy_config() method\n\nKEY PROCESSES:\n\n1. Configuration Fetch & Load\n  Get JSON config from API\/file\n  Parse into NetworkConfig object\n  Validate all settings\n\n2. Config Validation Process\n  Check DHCP:\n    - Valid IP\/subnet formats\n    - MAC addresses properly formatted\n  Check VLANs:\n    - IDs in valid range (1-4094)\n    - No duplicates\n    - Valid subnets\n  Verify DNS IPs\n  Validate firewall rules syntax\n\n3. Deployment Flow\n  For each network device:\n    Identify device type\n    Call appropriate deploy method\n    Log all actions\n    Handle any failures\n    Continue to next device\n\n4. Error Handling\n  Try\/catch around:\n    - Config loading\n    - Validation\n    - Each device deployment\n  Log all errors\n  Notify admin of failures","bgColorIndex":0}